{"article_id":"Fh1CaFrFKSj8mGx3","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"CHARLESTON , S.C. --","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"A former friend","depth":10},{"id":2,"text":"who had reconnected with the man","depth":11},{"id":3,"text":"accused of a shooting massacre inside a historic black church in Charleston , South Carolina ,","depth":11},{"id":4,"text":"said","depth":9},{"id":5,"text":"Dylann Roof had become an avowed racist .","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"Joey Meek reconnected with Roof a few weeks ago","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"and said","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"that","depth":10},{"id":9,"text":"while they got drunk together on vodka ,","depth":11},{"id":10,"text":"Roof began complaining","depth":12},{"id":11,"text":"that `` blacks were taking over the world ''","depth":13},{"id":12,"text":"and that `` someone needed to do something about it for the white race . ''","depth":13},{"id":13,"text":"Roof , 21 , is accused of fatally shooting nine people during a Bible study at The Emanuel African Methodist Episcopal Church in Charleston on Wednesday night ,","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"ripping out a piece of South Carolina 's civic heart","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"and adding to the ever-growing list of America 's racial casualties .","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"Police in Charleston said","depth":6},{"id":17,"text":"Roof was charged with nine counts of murder as well as possession of a weapon during the commission of a violent crime .","depth":6},{"id":18,"text":"Meek called the FBI","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"after recognizing Roof in the surveillance footage , down to the stained sweatshirt","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"he wore","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"while playing Xbox videogames in Meek 's home the morning of the attack .","depth":9},{"id":22,"text":"`` I did n't THINK","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"it was him .","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"I KNEW","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"it was him , ''","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"Meek told The Associated Press","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"after being interviewed by investigators .","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"correspondent Adriana Diaz reports","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"that a classmate reportedly described Roof as a `` pill popper ''","depth":10},{"id":30,"text":"who `` told racist jokes . ''","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"Those","depth":13},{"id":32,"text":"who knew Roof","depth":13},{"id":33,"text":"say","depth":12},{"id":34,"text":"they remember him talking about a scheme ,","depth":12},{"id":35,"text":"fueled by his segregationist ideals .","depth":12},{"id":36,"text":"Meek said","depth":11},{"id":37,"text":"Roof told him","depth":12},{"id":38,"text":"he wanted `` to start a civil war . ''","depth":12},{"id":39,"text":"Meek said during their reunion a few weeks ago , Roof told him","depth":11},{"id":40,"text":"that he had used birthday money from his parents","depth":13},{"id":41,"text":"to buy a .45-caliber Glock pistol","depth":13},{"id":42,"text":"and that he had `` a plan ''","depth":13},{"id":43,"text":"that was six months in the making .","depth":13},{"id":44,"text":"He did n't say","depth":12},{"id":45,"text":"what the plan was ,","depth":12},{"id":46,"text":"but Meek said","depth":12},{"id":47,"text":"it scared him enough","depth":13},{"id":48,"text":"that he took the gun out of Roof 's car","depth":14},{"id":49,"text":"and hid it in his house until the next day .","depth":14},{"id":50,"text":"Roof made incriminating statements","depth":8},{"id":51,"text":"indicating","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"he was involved in the shooting ,","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"has learned .","depth":7},{"id":54,"text":"Police captured Roof in Shelby , North Carolina ,","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"after a motorist spotted him at a traffic light on her way to work .","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"His apprehension ended an intense , hours-long manhunt .","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"Roof waived extradition","depth":8},{"id":58,"text":"and was back in Charleston on Thursday night ,","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"authorities said ,","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"with a bond hearing pending .","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"On Friday , South Carolina Gov . Nikki Haley told","depth":7},{"id":62,"text":"NBC 's `` Today '' show","depth":9},{"id":63,"text":"the shooter should get the death penalty .","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"`` We will absolutely will want him to have the death penalty , ''","depth":9},{"id":65,"text":"Haley said .","depth":9},{"id":66,"text":"Charleston officials announced a prayer vigil for Friday evening .","depth":7},{"id":67,"text":"The city 's mayor described the shooting at the church as an act of `` pure , pure concentrated evil . ''","depth":7},{"id":68,"text":"The victims included a state senator","depth":7},{"id":69,"text":"who doubled as the church 's minister ,","depth":7},{"id":70,"text":"three other pastors , a regional library manager , a high school coach and speech therapist , a government administrator , a college enrollment counselor and a recent college graduate","depth":7},{"id":71,"text":"- six women and three men","depth":8},{"id":72,"text":"who felt called to open their church to all .","depth":8},{"id":73,"text":"President Barack Obama called the tragedy yet another example of damage","depth":7},{"id":74,"text":"wreaked in America by guns .","depth":7},{"id":75,"text":"NAACP President and CEO Cornell William Brooks said","depth":8},{"id":76,"text":"`` there is no greater coward than a criminal","depth":9},{"id":77,"text":"who enters a house of God","depth":10},{"id":78,"text":"and slaughters innocent people . ''","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"Others bemoaned the loss to a church","depth":10},{"id":80,"text":"that has served as a bastion of black power for 200 years ,","depth":11},{"id":81,"text":"despite efforts by white supremacists","depth":12},{"id":82,"text":"to wipe it out .","depth":12},{"id":83,"text":"`` Of all cities , in Charleston , to have a horrible hateful person go into the church","depth":12},{"id":84,"text":"and kill people there","depth":15},{"id":85,"text":"to pray and worship with each other","depth":15},{"id":86,"text":"is something","depth":14},{"id":87,"text":"that is beyond any comprehension","depth":14},{"id":88,"text":"and is not explained , ''","depth":14},{"id":89,"text":"said Mayor Joseph P. Riley Jr.","depth":11},{"id":90,"text":"`` We are going to put our arms around that church and that church family . ''","depth":10},{"id":91,"text":"Gov . Haley :","depth":9},{"id":92,"text":"After S.C. church shooting suspect was in custody ,","depth":10},{"id":93,"text":"community could start to heal","depth":10},{"id":94,"text":"Surveillance video showed the gunman entering the church Wednesday night ,","depth":7},{"id":95,"text":"and a Snapchat video","depth":10},{"id":96,"text":"reportedly taken by one of the few survivors of the attack","depth":10},{"id":97,"text":"shows a small group of people","depth":10},{"id":98,"text":"gathered together inside the church .","depth":10},{"id":99,"text":"All of them are black except for one man .","depth":8},{"id":100,"text":"Charleston County Coroner Rae Wilson said","depth":9},{"id":101,"text":"he initially did n't appear threatening .","depth":9},{"id":102,"text":"`` The suspect entered the group","depth":10},{"id":103,"text":"and was accepted by them ,","depth":11},{"id":104,"text":"as they believed","depth":12},{"id":105,"text":"that he wanted to join them in this Bible study , ''","depth":12},{"id":106,"text":"she said .","depth":9},{"id":107,"text":"Then , `` he became very aggressive and violent . ''","depth":7},{"id":108,"text":"It 's not clear whether Roof had any connection to the 16 white supremacist organizations","depth":6},{"id":109,"text":"operating in South Carolina ,","depth":6},{"id":110,"text":"but he appears to be a `` disaffected white supremacist , ''","depth":7},{"id":111,"text":"based on his Facebook page ,","depth":7},{"id":112,"text":"said Richard Cohen , president of Southern Poverty Law Center in Montgomery , Alabama .","depth":6},{"id":113,"text":"On his Facebook page , Roof displayed the flags of defeated white-ruled regimes ,","depth":5},{"id":114,"text":"posing with a Confederate flags plate on his car","depth":6},{"id":115,"text":"and wearing a jacket with stitched-on flag patches from apartheid-era South Africa and Rhodesia ,","depth":7},{"id":116,"text":"which is now black-led Zimbabwe .","depth":7},{"id":117,"text":"Diaz reports","depth":5},{"id":118,"text":"that Roof was arrested in February at a mall in Columbia , South Carolina","depth":7},{"id":119,"text":"- charged with felony drug possession .","depth":7},{"id":120,"text":"He was wearing all black","depth":8},{"id":121,"text":"and suspicious employees called police .","depth":9},{"id":122,"text":"They found Roof with strips of the drug suboxone","depth":10},{"id":123,"text":"- often abused ,","depth":11},{"id":124,"text":"but typically used","depth":12},{"id":125,"text":"to treat opiate addiction .","depth":12},{"id":126,"text":"The mall banned him from the premises","depth":8},{"id":127,"text":"but he was arrested","depth":9},{"id":128,"text":"for trespassing there in April .","depth":9},{"id":129,"text":"Spilling blood inside a black church","depth":9},{"id":130,"text":"- especially `` Mother Emanuel , ''","depth":10},{"id":131,"text":"founded in 1816 -","depth":10},{"id":132,"text":"evoked painful memories nationwide , a reminder","depth":9},{"id":133,"text":"that black churches so often have been the targets of racist violence .","depth":9},{"id":134,"text":"A church founder , Denmark Vesey , was hanged","depth":10},{"id":135,"text":"after trying to organize a slave revolt in 1822 ,","depth":10},{"id":136,"text":"and white landowners burned the church in revenge ,","depth":10},{"id":137,"text":"leaving parishioners to worship underground until after the Civil War .","depth":10},{"id":138,"text":"The congregation rebuilt","depth":10},{"id":139,"text":"and grew stronger ,","depth":10},{"id":140,"text":"eventually winning campaigns for voting rights and political representation .","depth":9},{"id":141,"text":"Its lead pastor , state Sen. Clementa Pinckney","depth":12},{"id":142,"text":"- among the dead -","depth":12},{"id":143,"text":"recalled his church 's history in a 2013 sermon ,","depth":11},{"id":144,"text":"saying","depth":11},{"id":145,"text":"`` we do n't see ourselves as just a place","depth":13},{"id":146,"text":"where we come to worship ,","depth":13},{"id":147,"text":"but as a beacon and as a bearer of the culture . ''","depth":12},{"id":148,"text":"`` What the church is all about , ''","depth":12},{"id":149,"text":"Pinckney said ,","depth":12},{"id":150,"text":"is the `` freedom","depth":12},{"id":151,"text":"to be fully what God intends us to be","depth":13},{"id":152,"text":"and have equality in the sight of God .","depth":13},{"id":153,"text":"And sometimes you got to make noise","depth":12},{"id":154,"text":"to do that .","depth":12},{"id":155,"text":"Sometimes you may have to die like Denmark Vesey","depth":12},{"id":156,"text":"to do that . ''","depth":12},{"id":157,"text":"Pinckney , 41 , was a married father of two and a Democrat","depth":9},{"id":158,"text":"who spent 19 years in the South Carolina legislature","depth":10},{"id":159,"text":"after he was first elected at 23 ,","depth":11},{"id":160,"text":"becoming the youngest member of the House .","depth":11},{"id":161,"text":"The other victims were Cynthia Hurd , 54 ; Tywanza Sanders , 26 ; Myra Thompson , 59 ; Ethel Lance , 70 ; Susie Jackson , 87 ; and the reverends DePayne Middleton Doctor , 49 ; Sharonda Singleton , 45 ; and Daniel Simmons Sr. , 74 .","depth":7},{"id":162,"text":"U.S. Attorney General Loretta Lynch said","depth":6},{"id":163,"text":"the attack would be investigated as a hate crime .","depth":6}],"relations":[{"parent":327,"left":0,"right":326,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":326,"left":270,"right":325,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"pa